description:
&lt;p&gt;Liverpool Women’s is one of only two specialist Foundation Trusts in the UK dedicated to the healthcare of women, babies and their families&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for an enthusiastic and motivated Sonographer to join our busy, friendly and supportive team in the Imaging Department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Suitable candidates for this post will be HCPC registered qualified Sonographers or equivalent. You will be a key member of the Imaging team you will have the opportunity to demonstrate and develop your skills and expertise in obstetrics, gynaecology and general ultrasound as well as partake in some radiography duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to be able to work independently demonstrating a high level of competence and you will need to demonstrate excellent communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We value teamwork and are committed to training and development. We are also actively involved in the ultrasound training of student Sonographers and clinicians from a multi-professional background (both medically and non-medically qualified staff).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameKatie QualeyJob titleLead SonographerEmail addresskatie.qualey@lwh.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mrs Marianne Hamer Clinical Lead for Imaging Marianne.hamer@lwh.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
